      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "Design Rationale"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Safe mode exists because code items execute automatically. A broken view, library, or event handler can prevent normal operation. Safe mode provides a recovery path without requiring external tools."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "The emergency REPL loading (Tier 3 of "
        },
        [
          ":item-ref",
          {
            "s": "c0c0c0c0-0023-0000-0000-000000000000"
          },
          {
            "s": "Error Handling"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": ") provides a lighter-weight recovery — the REPL appears even when views break, without needing to restart in safe mode. Safe mode is the nuclear option when even the REPL is broken."
        }
      ],
